places.perex: Fantastic way to get to know the town if you have kids who'd be tired of walking. 45 minutes ride in historical touristic train.

places.name: Rancho Lorilar
places.perex: Explore the countryside with knowledgeable guide on the back of a horse. You're gonna love it!

places.name: Museo Infantil Trampolin
places.perex: Touchy-feely exhibits such as earthquake machines and volcano simulations. Science, ecology, children's rights, that all can kids learn here!

places.name: La Reyna Dominicana
places.perex: Give them a call and they'll arrange a cab for you. Unique store selling cigars and jewelry.

places.name: Marine Life Experience
places.perex: Get as close to the wildlife as possible - Marine Life Experience will make it happen for you!

places.name: Scape 2 Cap Cana
places.perex: Adventure center in the Cap Cana that can provide you with a tour, zipline, horseback riding, diving etc. Check them out!

places.name: Calle El Sol
places.perex: Manhattan of Santo Domingo! Colorful crowd buying stuff in picturesque shops.

places.name: The Cacao Trail
places.perex: You have wonderful option to learn about the secrets about the "food of the Gods". Tour is entertaining, informative and tasty!

places.name: Fun City
places.perex: Certainly the best deal on the island. For definitely not a lot of money you'll get unlimited use of all tracks and other perks.

places.name: Rancho Lobo Gris
places.perex: If you want to get to know the outback Dominican Republic, the best you can do is to visit this ranch.

places.name: Turtle Dive Center
places.perex: Lots of above and under water fun. The staff is very attentive.

places.name: Epona Ranch
places.perex: Very well taken care of horses with whom you can discover the treasures of Samaná peninsula.

places.name: Estancia Natura at Spirit Mountain
places.perex: Thoughtfully designed eco-route can teach you about sustainable organic farming etc. Learn to appreciate nature and what comes out of it!

places.name: The Whales
places.perex: Place famous for whale watching. Opt for bigger boat so that you spot them better when the water is rough (which is very often here).

places.name: La Atarazana
places.perex: This small area is home to original 16th century houses where now art galleries reside.

places.name: Public Beach of Dominicus at Bayahibe
places.perex: Highly valued white sand beach with crystal clear water. Like everywhere around the island.

places.name: Caleta Beach
places.name_suffix: La Romana, Dominican Republic, République Dominicaine
places.perex: Beach frequented mostly by locals and attended by vendors selling fresh fish.

places.name: Cabo Cabron
places.perex: Remote part of the island that is hard to get to - either a rough road through Los Tocones or by boat from Playa Rincon.

places.name: Playa Mariposa
places.name_suffix: La Romana, Dominican Republic, République Dominicaine
places.perex: Take a walk from Canto de la Playa, because maneuvring the boat through the reef might be dangerous.

places.name: El Choco National Park
places.perex: Belongs among the newest parks in the country. It's main attributes are jungle, caves and trails.

places.name: St. George Wreck
places.perex: 80m long steel freighter now serves under water as a home for plenty of marine life, from which the most notable is barracuda. Find her!

places.name: Juan Ponce de Leon Home
places.perex: Home, that looks more like fortified building, to the 16th century explorer who found Florida.

places.name: La Entrada Beach
places.perex: Fabulous beach for those who seek deserted swimming. This is assured mainly during the week.

places.name: Monumento San Pedro
places.name_suffix: San Pedro de Macorís, République Dominicaine

places.name: La Marina Casa de Campo
places.name_suffix: La Romana, Dominican Republic, République Dominicaine

places.name_suffix: San Pedro de Macorís, République Dominicaine

places.name_suffix: La Romana, Dominican Republic, République Dominicaine

places.name: St Stanislaus Church
places.name_suffix: La Romana, Dominican Republic, République Dominicaine

places.name: Diamant Beach
places.perex: Circle lagoon of turquoise water blending smoothly into the ocean. Nobody's here on weekdays.

places.name: Casa de Francia
places.perex: Residence of Hernán Cortés, the conqueror of the Aztecs. Although visitors are not allowed to enter since it is French embassy now, you can…

places.name: Museum of History and Geography
places.perex: Its biggest attraction is car in which the dictator Trujillo was assassinated.

places.name: Plaza de la Cultura
places.perex: Nice area of the city. Museum quartier, thater and library, shady trees...

places.name: Los Patos Beach
places.perex: Idyllic sandy beach where you can enjoy swimimming, surfing and much more!

places.name: Goat Island National Park
places.perex: Island enclosed by saltwater Lake Enriquillo. Interesting place for many reasons - the lowest part of all Carribean, lots of reptile species…

places.name: José del Carmen Ramírez National Park
places.perex: Park was established to protect what was left of the virgin forest. It has trails for adventurous hikers.

places.name: Sierra De Baoruco National Park
places.perex: This park bordering the Republic of Haiti contains some very high mountains and satisfies those who crave for adventure tourism.

places.name: Playa Caleton
places.perex: Oh, how beautiful this place is! Mostly attended by locals, so we're revealing their secret.

places.name: Luna del Caribe
places.perex: Roots and traditions of Dominican culture are revealed in folklore show accompanied by great food on the buffet.

places.name: The Cord House
places.perex: Rumored to be the first European residence in Americas and also the first one with two floors!

places.name: Armando Bermúdez National Park
places.perex: First national park of the Dominican Republic that has the highest mountain of the Carribean - Pico Duarte.

places.name: House of Bastidas
places.perex: Residence of king's tax collector. To admire there is large patio adorned with Roman arches.

places.name: La Sirena
places.perex: Best diving spot on the island! Clear warm water, ceilings like sugar icing, limestone creations out of a fairytale and plenty of…

places.name: Saint Barbara's Church
places.perex: Overlooked old church with beautiful statues inside. Worth seeing if interested in religious places.

places.name: Funtastico
places.perex: If you are really bored or your kids demand it, visit Funtastico and play some games.

places.name: Tobacco Museum
places.name_suffix: Santiago de los Caballeros, République Dominicaine
places.perex: Discover the importance of tobacco to the economy of Santiago. History of tobacco growing, different manufacturing methods and more.

places.name: Sundial
places.perex: Sundial built in 1753 for the officials sitting in the officies of what is now Museo de las Casas Reales. Still working!

places.name: Hickory
places.perex: Since 1986 corals have grown on this 144-foot long wreck. Amazing diving place!

places.name: Cofres Beach
places.perex: Named after famous pirate, this beach is a bit choppy too. Luxury condos and resorts to satisfy all your desires.
